<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>

<p>Phoenix is a frontend framework for Mediacorp. This is a documentation of the grid that is created for the project. Before we begin the implementation, let&#8217;s first discuss some common terminologies that all parties have agreed to use.</p>

<h2 id="structureblocks">Structure Blocks</h2>

<p>Structure blocks determine the structure of the a section. Multiple structure blocks would make up a page. </p>

<p>Examples of structure blocks are the full width (<code>.l-12</code>) block and the content-sidebar (.<code>l-2up--8-4</code>) block, or even the 4-column block (<code>.l-4up</code>). </p>
